## Setup

1) Add keys to ~/.ssh/elephantdb and ~/.ssh/elephantdb.pub. These will be installed on EDB server.
2) Create ~/.pallet/config.clj with contents:
(defpallet
  :services {
              :elephantdb-deploy {
                         :provider "aws-ec2"
                         :identity "XXXX"
                         :credential "XXXXX"
                         }

              :elephantdb-data {
                         :blobstore-provider "aws-s3"
                         :provider "aws-ec2"
                         :identity "XXXX"
                         :credential "XXXX"
                         }
             }
    :environment {:algorithms
                  {:lift-fn pallet.core/parallel-lift
                   :converge-fn pallet.core/parallel-adjust-node-counts}})

3) Add configuration files for your ring to ../deploy/conf
   There's an example in ../deploy/conf/dev2

## Usage

To provision a cluster:
$ lein run --start --ring dev2

To deploy new ../deploy/conf/dev2/ changes to an existing cluster.
$ lein run --start --ring dev2




